At least 10 people were left injured following a collision between a taxi and two light motor vehicles on Dr Belcher Road in Bloemfontein in the Free State on Wednesday morning. Upon arrival, paramedics found the taxi lying on its side on the side of the road and two light motor vehicles were found in the middle of the road. “Ten people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. Fortunately, no serious injuries or fatalities were found at the scene,” ER24 said in a statement. All patients were assessed at the scene before they were transported to various hospitals for further treatment. The cause of the incident is still unknown and will form part of a SAPS investigation. -TNA Reporter